{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"body":"FIX 3 (re-target migration) BUILT + DRY-RUN VALIDATED on a clone copy (commit 71759efa) — live store UNTOUCHED:\n- scripts/retarget_jira_project.py: clears bindings.json + prev_snapshot.json (with backup; optional --strip-tags), dry-run by default.\n- Validated on a hardlinked clone of the DIG-bound store with the FIXED reconciler: dry-run plan went 1415 mutations (1017 DIG) -> after migration 398 outbound creates, 0 DIG. Every active ticket would re-create fresh in REB.\n- docs/jira-sync-setup.md gains a 'Re-targeting an existing store' section.\nPer user direction (build + dry-run first), the live cutover is NOT executed — awaiting review. A live pass before cutover safely REFUSES DIG (guard), so merging the schedule before cutover would just fail+alert; keep PR #20 auto-merge OFF until the live re-target is applied."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782420220214919001,"uuid":"09849901-5238-4776-bf86-3eeaf3f8d1e0"}